                    <span>I have read a lot of women's and Constitutional history, and still my jaw literally dropped open several times while reading this book. Her use of real scenarios made the book readable and enjoyable. People have said  lately that we are focused too much on our rights and not our  responsibilities; it's scary to see that whether women must bear the  responsibilities of citizenship is still in many ways an open question.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Readable, well documented and informative</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
